<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-649-844  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 649 844.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  July 9 1990 n277 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Database control. (Thailand Ministry of the Interior's CentralPopulation Database Center)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hoffman, Thomas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Thailand is developing a centralized population database system inorder to track and cross-correlate important information on eachof its 55 million citizens.andP;  In summer 1990, the Ministry of theInterior will introduce the Central Population Database Center.andO;An important component of the system will be the PopulationIdentification Number, a computerized ID card system.andP;  A card willbe issued to adults 15 years and older, representing 60 percent ofthe population.andP;  Cards will be used to verify a person's identity,with magnetic strips for bar code scanning planned for the nearfuture.andP;  The system will run on three Cyber 960 mainframes and twoCyber 830 multiprocessors, with disk capacity more than 100gigabytes.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Population GroupsData BasesThailandTracking SystemsBar-Code ScannersMainframe Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>